title: Jeremy Corbyn stripped of 'Right Honourable' title after missing meeting with the Queen
text: Jeremy Corbyn has been stripped of his "Right Honourable" title on the orders of the Queen's advisers, after Number 10 wrongly implied the Labour leader had joined the Privy Council. Mr Corbyn was described as "Right Honourable" on Parliament's website until late last week. However, after he missed the first meeting of the Privy Council since the summer holidays with the Queen last Thursday, the "Rt Hon" title was removed from Mr Corbyn's page on Parliament's website.
